@@TJvFileInfo
<TITLEIMG TJvFileInfo>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.System.FilesAndFolders
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  Retrieve info on a file, such as type, attribute, modifier and icon.
Description
  TJvFileInfo is a non-visible component that provides you with information on a particular file. 
  File information such as type, attribute, modifier, icon can be retrieved with the published 
  properties.

  To get information on the a file you should:

  * drop a TJvFileInfo on a form or data module.
  * set the property FileName to an existing file on your computer.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFileInfo.Attributes
Summary
  Holds the file attributes as an integer value.
Description
  Attributes holds the file attributes as an integer value. The value returned is the same as the one
  returned by GetFileAttributes(PChar(FileName)).
See Also
  AttrString
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFileInfo.AttrString
Summary
  Returns the attributes of a file or directory as a \string.
Description
  This Read-Only property returns the attributes of a file or directory as one \string.  For a file 
  that has an attribute of Archive the result is "A".  For a combination of attributes such as 
  (Archive + Hidden + System), the result is "AHS".
  
  The possible attributes are:
  <TABLE>
    Attribute     Resulting string
    ---------     ----------------
    Normal        (no AttrString)
    Archive       A
    Compressed    C
    Directory     D
    Hidden        H
    Readonly      R
    System        S
  </TABLE>
  
  Combinations of attributes will be returned in the order specified in the table.
See Also
  Attributes
